U.K. Gilts Extend Drop After Bond Auction, S&P Outlook on Rate Increases

-- B y   K e i t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 
2011-05-04T10:06:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/u-k-gilts-extend-drop-after-bond-auction-s-p-outlook-on-rate-increases.html
U.K. gilts extended declines after the
Debt Management Office auctioned  government bonds  and  Standard &
Poor’s  said an interest-rate increase was “almost certain”
over the next three months.  The yield on the 10-year gilt rose four basis points to
3.46 as of 11 a.m. in  London .  The debt agency sold 3.25 billion pounds of 2025 bonds at a
yield of 3.835 percent. Investors demanded 1.25 times the amount
of securities on offer.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Keith Campbell at 
 k.campbell@bloomberg.net  